  <data name="HelpTitle" xml:space="preserve"><value>PureAudio - User Guide</value></data>
  <data name="HelpIntro" xml:space="preserve"><value>PureAudio is a bit-perfect audio player for high-quality music playback.</value></data>
  <data name="HelpPlayback" xml:space="preserve"><value>Playback Controls: Use ◄◄ (Previous), ►/❚❚ (Play/Pause), ■ (Stop), ►► (Next) to control playback.</value></data>
  <data name="HelpWasapi" xml:space="preserve"><value>WASAPI Mode: Toggle between Shared and Exclusive modes. Exclusive mode provides bit-perfect output.</value></data>
  <data name="HelpGapless" xml:space="preserve"><value>Gapless: When enabled, tracks transition without silence between them.</value></data>
  <data name="HelpLibrary" xml:space="preserve"><value>Library: Browse your music folders, double-click to add tracks to the playlist.</value></data>
  <data name="HelpPlaylist" xml:space="preserve"><value>Playlist: Reorder tracks with Up/Down, remove with X, or clear all with the basket icon.</value></data>
